Description: Sherd of pottery shallow dish with wide flat rim and flat foot offset minimally from the wall; small spool-shaped attachments on outside of rim for decoration, three seemingly broken off; one of the broken surfaces is burnt; a smear of paint on the foot (as on 1965,0930.188 and 189) is akin to marks indicating joins, though it appears ancient.
Curator's comments: Close to 1965,0930.188 and 189 but with slightly different profile.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GO.677)
